description: Code Connect rules for mapping stable reusable Figma components to React components in this repo. Use for `.figma.tsx` or `.figma.js` work, not for page implementation.
globs: ["src/**/*.figma.tsx", "src/**/*.figma.js", "src/components/**/*.tsx"]
alwaysApply: false
---

# Intent

Use Code Connect only for reusable component mapping.

In this repo:

- screen implementation belongs in React page and component files
- workflow and validation belong in local skill files and repo rules
- Code Connect belongs only to stable reusable components

# Rules

- Do not create Code Connect files for components in `src/pages/`.
- Do not map one-off demo sections or temporary page markup.
- Keep mappings aligned with the real React props and slots.
- Prefer colocating `.figma.tsx` files with the reusable component they describe.
- Do not invent props or variants just to mirror Figma.
- If a component is still unstable, postpone the mapping and keep the screen work in normal React code.

# Validation

- target Figma node is a reusable component or component set
- target code file is a reusable component, not a page
- mapping reflects the actual public component API
